Happy 10 year debut anniversary to Orange Is The New Black @oitnb.

Thank you @ijnej for creating a world that changed the lives of many people- myself included. 

My very first recurring role came from this show, so it will always mark a special time in my life as an actor.

I remember sitting in waiting at my audition for @jennifer_euston_casting and getting a call about a job offer with the NBA. I got off the call and said to myself that this would be my last acting audition- as my career in entertainment hosting was moving at a rate that acting just wasn’t. 

That “last audition” turned into 2 seasons, countless memories with people i will never forget, and re-lit the fire on a childhood dream that I almost let go. 

Thank you all for being great artist and even better people. It was a joy and honor to come play in the sandbox with you all. Much love. 🧡🖤 🍊

Last night, the world lost one of the most interesting and loving person’s I’ve ever encountered. 

@scottgruenwald it’s hard to capture our friendship in a single post but I think these 3 make an attempt. 

1. You are a member of my 1st TV family and I’ll remember you taking me under your wing and teaching me new things daily. The way you welcomed me, and spoke life and positivity over me- became a staple of how I welcome others when we work together. Just share love, acceptance, and knowledge. You had such a passion for knowledge and curiosity for the world around us and shared that daily. 

2. We all went to dinner after we wrapped and were the only ones with our sunglasses on. You said, “I want to be cool like you” and I said “It’s an attitude- embody cool” then we got this candid 😂😎

3. This is the first rap I think I ever freestyle on TV and you supplied the beatbox. As our oldest cast member you showed me that youth was a spirit and this video always reminds me to stay young, never take yourself too seriously, and live in the moment. 

You will be missed my dear friend. Don’t be out here haunting people and sh*t- I know you’d want to. Lol Really rest in peace. 🕊️

@aaronsagers @realzakbagans @travelchannel Thank you for bringing us together. These moments i cherish forever. 🙏🏾

First time attending @hapawards. 

Was honored to be apart of the comedy writing team for @thegenzone alongside my writing partner and friend @koreywebbt. We’d stay up writing jokes through the night- sometimes falling asleep on the floor, and wake up the next morning hoping to God we had fresh inspiration so that we’d meet the deadlines. Love you brethren. 

@damiendouglas_ You’re a powerhouse. Thank you for the opportunity and entrusting us to bring another element to a show that was dear to your heart. You’re a leader who’s only demand was honesty and excellence. 

To our amazing host @lovelikejhoney, you carry this show day in and day out. You devote your all to learning the facts, conducting real interviews, and presenting politics in a way that generation z can receive it- raw, real, and sometimes ridiculous. I appreciate you. 

#hapaawards #hapaawards2023 #TheGenzone

Last night, @thegenzone took home the HAPA award for Best Streaming News/Talk Show! 🏆 @hapawards 

Immense love and gratitude to our phenomenal host @lovelikejhoney- you're the heartbeat of this show, and your personality coupled with your interviews light up the screen. 

To our brilliant producers/ directors @damiendouglas_ @seanmillercinema your leadership and creativity gives this show wings. You never backed off your vision and made sure we all stayed committed to delivering truth. 

Special nod to our head comedy writer @kayewinks and my comedy writing partner @koreywebbt —those late nights diving into politics to formulate comedy and hit deadlines were worth every sleepless minute. Here's to more truth and even more laughter! 🥂📺 

#HAPAAwards #TheGenZone #TVTalkShow #AwardShows #Writer #Comedian #Actor #ComedyWriter

Swipe left to catch some behind-the-scenes captured by @reb213photo and @oliviawong11. 

Big thanks to @HAPAAwards for the recognition and the unforgettable evening. Shoutout to the incredible @thegenzone team who make the dream work, and a special thanks to my lovely lady for making the night even more special. Here's to many more! 🥂📸 #HAPAAwards #BehindTheScenes #TheGenZone #AwardNight"

Picasso once said, "Art is the lie that enables us to realize the truth."

🎬 Between takes and reality, there's a space where an actor must merge multiple truths- their own and the characters. 

The art of storytelling blurs the lines between the worlds we create on screen and the ones we live off of it. 

The hope is that the artist and audience finds a very real piece of themselves in the art.

I’m the product of perseverance and a lot of peoples prayers. To everyone who’s ever believed in me- may you always remember that your words and support have the power to positively impact others. Thank you for choosing me to be one of them. 

Honored to be back for the next season of @sistasonbet by @tylerperry directed by @armaniortiz. I want to thank my fellow cast-mates whose artistry and hard-work laid the foundation for this opportunity to even be a possibility. 

Thank you to my team: @tandmtalentmanagement @pedro_tapia___  @cesdtalent, and @katzpublicrelations for sticking by side through swings of this business and believing in me. 

Thank you @kimcolemancasting for seeing me over the years and giving me a shot at this one. I’m infinitely thankful. 

To @tylerperry, thank you for honoring your gift, it’s made room for other people’s dreams to exist. 

When I started acting in high school my dream was to one day get to this point. Nothing happened overnight, and God made sure I utilized every talent  on the way here. For that, I’m all the more thankful. Whatever you do, don’t quit. 

The race is not given to the swift or to the strong but to the one who endures to the end... Ecclesiastes 9:11
